nsions for profane democracy. A demonstration of literary criticism practiced as a fecund interdisciplinary activity, Loukson's study lays the foundation for post-apartheid criticism different from post-colonial criticism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHomosexuality in literature. 0aLiterature and societyzSouth AfricaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiterature and societyzSouth AfricaxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolitics and literaturezSouth AfricaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitics and literaturezSouth AfricaxHistoryy21st century. 0aPost-apartheid erazSouth Africa. 0aRace relations in literature. 0aSouth African literature (English)xHistory and criticism. 4aBritish Studies. 4aDemocracy. 4aGender. 4aGeneral Literature Studies. 4aHegemony. 4aHomosexuality. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aPerceptions. 4aPost-Apartheid Narrative. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aQueer Theory. 4aRacism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aBritish Studies.  aDemocracy.  aGender.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aHegemony.  aHomosexuality.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aPerceptions.  aPost-Apartheid Narrative.  aPostcolonialism.  aQueer Theory.  aRacism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 